definitions.definition: The plural number. In English, referring to more or less than one of something.
A word in the form in which it potentially refers to something other than one person or thing; and other than two things if the language has a dual form.
examples: The plural of 'cat' is 'cats', but the plural of 'child' is 'children'.

definitions.definition: A person with some form of multiplicity , particularly dissociative identity disorder .

main_definition: ( grammar , uncountable ) The plural number. In English, referring to more or less than one of something.
secondary_definitions: ( grammar , countable ) A word in the form in which it potentially refers to something other than one person or thing; and other than two things if the language has a dual form.
( multiplicity , countable ) A person with some form of multiplicity , particularly dissociative identity disorder .
